709399f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, north from W. 25th Street. Note the 6-story Coogan Building at the N. E. corner of
26th Street.
The old "El" line, running overhead will be removed
in 1938.
January 29,1928
Views 1,2
P. L. Snerr

the city.
December 24, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, north from West 27th Street.
December 24, 1936.

Sixth Avenue, east side, north from W. 25th St., as photographed before and after the removal of the old "El" line. The Empire State Building towers over the district in the later view. At the left appears the Hotel McAlpin at Greeley Square.
